  "title": "Director, Recovery & Reorganisation",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Lead end-to-end restructuring and recovery engagements, including judicial management, liquidation, receivership, individual voluntary arrangements, schemes of arrangement, and individual bankruptcy.</li><li>Diagnose root causes of financial distress and develop practical, realistic, and implementable turnaround plans.</li><li>Manage key stakeholders: banks, creditors, boards, shareholders, legal counsel, regulators.</li><li>Prepare cash flow analysis, viability reviews, and restructuring proposals.</li><li>Oversee statutory filings, compliance, asset realisation, and case administration.</li><li>Prepare creditor reports and restructuring proposals.</li><li>Provide support to business development and client relationship initiatives.</li><li>Supervise, coach and lead a team to deliver high-quality outcomes.</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 10–12 years of relevant experience</li><li>Professional qualification: Degree in Accounting, Finance, or Business; professional qualification (CPA, CA, CFA) preferred.</li><li>Appointment as a liquidator with sound knowledge of Singapore insolvency law (IRDA) and related legal/regulatory frameworks.</li><li>Strong financial modelling skills, proven ability to assess liquidity, business viability, and capital structure.</li><li>Strong written and verbal communication skills.</li></ul><p><br />If you are ready to join a dynamic team and help businesses succeed while growing your own career, we want to hear from you. Apply now and take the next step in your professional journey with FKT!</p><p>Please do <strong>NOT</strong> include NRIC/FIN or any national identifiers, Photo, DOB, Age and Spouse/Family Information in your CV/Resume and we reserve the right to reject any application that contains the above.  For more details, please refer to our website, www.fookontan.com/careers for our Data Protection Notice for Job Applicants.</p><p><em>We regret to inform that only short-listed candidates will be notified.</em></p>",
